reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Albert Z.', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105400271334770402256/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgaskIPryhn1W50hwBQGhqBRLCr5tzbgdDd9CQZ8eQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Bought 3 bottles of red wine, different  brands, all of which I consistently buy at various stores and very satisfied with my purchases.  When I noticed the prices were lower at plaza liquors hewlett, I gladly bought the three bottles.
When I opened the first bottle, surprisingly the color was a more transparent pink rather than the deep burgundy I am accustomed to. Ok different vintage maybe. But no smell, no taste, no rich full body aroma. Very disappointed but could happen once in a while so proceed to open second bottle, again different brand. SHOCKED same result. Third bottle same result. What a coincidence? Different brands, same result!
Only logical conclusion can be that this store sells FAKE WINE with FAKE LABELS albeit very convincing from the external appearance.
I should mention that I had no problem in the past when purchasing kosher Israeli wines from the same store.
Anyway I did get my money back for 2 out 3 bottles, I had poured the first one down the drain.
Do yourself a favor and steer away from this store if you like to get what you pay for.
Live and learn. / A.', 'time': 1613406879}, {'author_name': 'Dan B', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111787374709133964945/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GgJqfbgGimtYymAacaQrmJabhgS5Igbvekxk5kIVMM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Unbelievable selection of wines scotches Bourbons vodkas and all sorts of other spirits with a wonderful staff.', 'time': 1611954565}, {'author_name': 'Bill Brooks', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103918987753088827033/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AATXAJzMmw9a_QeKYcU4whpRRk3pr_alD9s_toOnFt0q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4', 'rating': 3, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': "It's great, they have way too much stuff so it's a little hard to maneuver the isles. Love the Butcher Bar! The atmosphere is really nice and cozy, the decor is cool, and the food never disappoints. I used to come here a lot couple of years ago but yesterday was my first time back in a while. Everything is as I remember.

The menu is on the smaller side but it offers all kinds of goodness. We got the carved board with the burned ends (the best item on the menu!), brisket (falling apart and super juicy), and the pork belly (tasty but a bit crispy for my taste). We also ordered a side of french fries (fresh cut and amazing) and the house slaw (no twist, just regular coleslaw but made to perfection). We also ordered two cocktails- the cucumber refresher (was very refreshing indeed but no alcohol to it at all) and the blood red sangria (which was pretty good). The three of us split everything and we left happy and with full bellies. Definitely will be coming back!', 'time': 1473697230}, {'author_name': 'Laura Raymond', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110680126158884745788/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh7zr6vDQtktYjszEPDm6lI3wpMrkMbGQQyqREj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Good customer service', 'time': 1614020323}]

reviews: [{'author_name': 'Tylon Turner', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110322639563580978948/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiRyiig275a4r_bPEIcup7GILjPKqiOkC8DHY02Yw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': '3 months ago', 'text': 'best-selling price in my neighborhood all good...IPAs selection off the hook..liquor sold cold there too what more can i tell ya', 'time': 1648499003}, {'author_name': 'Wanderlust Maverick', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100646859618772062298/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GiexpF0u76xiI7B24pP6blVwSug4rkf7hsm6t65i4k=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo', 'rating': 1, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'The owner at this liquor store is extremely rude and makes fun of his costumers. I just went to purchase a bottle of wine and grabbed two from the fridge, they weren\'t priced marked so I asked him for a price, rather than telling me or scanning it he just pointed me towards the location where they are priced on the shelves (not the fridge) with a very dismissive attitude as if I\'m bothering him (there were no other costumers in the store by the way). Without saying much I went over to look for the prices. As I was making my mind up between two bottles I looked for the second bottle\'s price and after looking around the white whine section for a few minutes, I couldn\'t find the second bottle on the shelves. After a few minutes of me going through all the shelves I gave up and just decided to take both bottles to the register and ask him for the second bottle\'s price. When I asked he blew up and yelled at me that all bottles are priced on the shelves, I told him I looked for it but couldn\'t find it. He then said "well that second bottle is over there (a completely different section)". Long story short he said "if you need a price you ask me" which is the first thing I did but he just didn\'t want to be bothered. He then charged me for both bottles and when I told him wasn\'t buying both bottles he got even more upset and told me that he doesn\'t like me (so at this point it was obvious it\'s a personal problem...this is a liquor store in my neighborhood and - he might not like me for other reasons; his personal reason...I don\'t want to assume but it\'s clear- I support local business rather than buying for cheaper at Costco). He yelled at me and even made fun of me for "walking around like a mouse looking for stuff" and that I should ask...which is what I did in the first place. He clearly saw me looking all over for a price for the second bottle and didn\'t bother ask me if i needed help (even when the store (a very small one) was empty) and when finally gave up looking for the price he blows up. I was confused but before I left he yelled at me F...U\nto me this is a very bad costumer service his attitude clearly demonstrates that he couldn\'t care less about his costumers. If items aren\'t clearly marked at the section you grab them you have to go to a different section to check for the price...and that\'s fine but if you can\'t find the item after you\'ve asked, a business owner should not get mad at you for asking and even worse to make fun of you when he or she clearly sees that you are lost or need help navigating through the store.\nDo yourself a favor and shop somewhere else, support a business that welcomes you as a customer and treats you with respect and dignity. But if you want to look around and choose a bottle of wine (what a crazy idea right?) you cannot do that. The entire place is safe guarded with strong plastic walls and locks. You walk in, and the entire store is blocked off from you, you can only see the bottles from a distance. I understand the safety issue, fine!

Then he brought a bottle that I asked for and there‚Äôs no description on this wine bottle so I wanted to use an app I always use! He started having an attitude like it‚Äôs such a big problem I want to know what I‚Äôm going pay for and drink. Started yelling at me and we got into an argument.. then he said cash only! Which is not totally abnormal but after so many obstacles, cash only just seems like he doesn‚Äôt want people to buy anything :/

I feel like I sound bougie but if I was, I would have turned around once I saw the place. It‚Äôs really gritty. Which can be great! But in this case, the place doesn‚Äôt make you feel safe, the owner is so mean, and can‚Äôt properly and calmly buy a bottle of anything (unless you know what you want AND have cash).

A true nyc experience (not in a good way)!

- Love Maria,

But if you want to look around and choose a bottle of wine (what a crazy idea right?) you cannot do that. The entire place is safe guarded with strong plastic walls and locks. You walk in, and the entire store is blocked off from you, you can only see the bottles from a distance. I understand the safety issue, fine!

Then he brought a bottle that I asked for and there‚Äôs no description on this wine bottle so I wanted to use an app I always use! He started having an attitude like it‚Äôs such a big problem I want to know what I‚Äôm going pay for and drink. Started yelling at me and we got into an argument.. then he said cash only! Which is not totally abnormal but after so many obstacles, cash only just seems like he doesn‚Äôt want people to buy anything :/

I feel like I sound bougie but if I was, I would have turned around once I saw the place. It‚Äôs really gritty. Which can be great! But in this case, the place doesn‚Äôt make you feel safe, the owner is so mean, and can‚Äôt properly and calmly buy a bottle of anything (unless you know what you want AND have cash).

A true nyc experience (not in a good way)!

- Love Maria,

reviews:
[{'author_name': 'Bob Santero Agency', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105922450501704386540/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14GjWiZUdNrqAqpDJXfE5FnqTKBvJ5IOBZwhjbneoivg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 5, 'relative_time_description': 'a month ago', 'text': "Got some Santero Wine from Roci Wine & Liquor, the only store around that carries it.

My grandfather started the company years ago, and I trampled the grapes with my 10 year old feet.

Love the Butcher Bar! The atmosphere is really nice and cozy, the decor is cool, and the food never disappoints. I used to come here a lot couple of years ago but yesterday was my first time back in a while. Everything is as I remember.

The menu is on the smaller side but it offers all kinds of goodness. We got the carved board with the burned ends (the best item on the menu!), brisket (falling apart and super juicy), and the pork belly (tasty but a bit crispy for my taste). We also ordered a side of french fries (fresh cut and amazing) and the house slaw (no twist, just regular coleslaw but made to perfection). We also ordered two cocktails- the cucumber refresher (was very refreshing indeed but no alcohol to it at all) and the blood red sangria (which was pretty good). The three of us split everything and we left happy and with full bellies. Definitely will be coming back!', 'time': 1473697230}, {'author_name': 'Laura Raymond', 'author_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110680126158884745788/reviews', 'language': 'en', 'profile_photo_url': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/AOh14Gh7zr6vDQtktYjszEPDm6lI3wpMrkMbGQQyqREj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2', 'rating': 4, 'relative_time_description': 'a year ago', 'text': 'Good customer service', 'time': 1614020323}]

1 check-in
Love the Butcher Bar! The atmosphere is really nice and cozy, the decor is cool, and the food never disappoints. I used to come here a lot couple of years ago but yesterday was my first time back in a while. Everything is as I remember.

The menu is on the smaller side but it offers all kinds of goodness. We got the carved board with the burned ends (the best item on the menu!), brisket (falling apart and super juicy), and the pork belly (tasty but a bit crispy for my taste). We also ordered a side of french fries (fresh cut and amazing) and the house slaw (no twist, just regular coleslaw but made to perfection). We also ordered two cocktails- the cucumber refresher (was very refreshing indeed but no alcohol to it at all) and the blood red sangria (which was pretty good). The three of us split everything and we left happy and with full bellies.
